{
  "video_id": "k4N2SxUZwiU",
  "title": "How I found a mythical boiling river in the Amazon | Andrés Ruzo",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13230.0,
      "end_time": 14666.0,
      "text": "As a boy in Lima,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14690.0,
      "end_time": 16801.0,
      "text": "my grandfather told me a legend"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16825.0,
      "end_time": 19790.0,
      "text": "of the Spanish conquest of Peru."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20700.0,
      "end_time": 23546.0,
      "text": "Atahualpa, emperor of the Inca, had been captured and killed."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23570.0,
      "end_time": 26553.0,
      "text": "Pizarro and his conquistadors had grown rich,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26577.0,
      "end_time": 29763.0,
      "text": "and tales of their conquest and glory had reached Spain"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29787.0,
      "end_time": 35162.0,
      "text": "and was bringing new waves of Spaniards, hungry for gold and glory."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36550.0,
      "end_time": 38953.0,
      "text": "They would go into towns and ask the Inca,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38977.0,
      "end_time": 42751.0,
      "text": "\"Where&#39;s another civilization we can conquer? Where&#39;s more gold?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42776.0,
      "end_time": 46155.0,
      "text": "And the Inca, out of vengeance, told them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 46648.0,
      "end_time": 48257.0,
      "text": "\"Go to the Amazon."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48767.0,
      "end_time": 51413.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ll find all the gold you want there."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51437.0,
      "end_time": 56150.0,
      "text": "In fact, there is a city called Paititi -- El Dorado in Spanish --"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 56175.0,
      "end_time": 58802.0,
      "text": "made entirely of gold.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 59303.0,
      "end_time": 61199.0,
      "text": "The Spanish set off into the jungle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 61223.0,
      "end_time": 64785.0,
      "text": "but the few that return come back with stories,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 65904.0,
      "end_time": 69711.0,
      "text": "stories of powerful shamans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 69735.0,
      "end_time": 72639.0,
      "text": "of warriors with poisoned arrows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 72663.0,
      "end_time": 76441.0,
      "text": "of trees so tall they blotted out the sun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 76465.0,
      "end_time": 81217.0,
      "text": "spiders that ate birds, snakes that swallowed men whole"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 81241.0,
      "end_time": 83525.0,
      "text": "and a river that boiled."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 85795.0,
      "end_time": 87779.0,
      "text": "All this became a childhood memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 87803.0,
      "end_time": 88962.0,
      "text": "And years passed."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 88986.0,
      "end_time": 91461.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m working on my PhD at SMU,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 91485.0,
      "end_time": 95389.0,
      "text": "trying to understand Peru&#39;s geothermal energy potential,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 95413.0,
      "end_time": 97459.0,
      "text": "when I remember this legend,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 97483.0,
      "end_time": 99332.0,
      "text": "and I began asking that question."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 100316.0,
      "end_time": 102863.0,
      "text": "Could the boiling river exist?"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 104140.0,
      "end_time": 106339.0,
      "text": "I asked colleagues from universities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 106363.0,
      "end_time": 107520.0,
      "text": "the government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 107544.0,
      "end_time": 109360.0,
      "text": "oil, gas and mining companies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 109610.0,
      "end_time": 111967.0,
      "text": "and the answer was a unanimous no."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 112459.0,
      "end_time": 114459.0,
      "text": "And this makes sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 115700.0,
      "end_time": 117698.0,
      "text": "You see, boiling rivers do exist in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 117722.0,
      "end_time": 120181.0,
      "text": "but they&#39;re generally associated with volcanoes."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 120649.0,
      "end_time": 122796.0,
      "text": "You need a powerful heat source"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 122820.0,
      "end_time": 126186.0,
      "text": "to produce such a large geothermal manifestation."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 126210.0,
      "end_time": 131414.0,
      "text": "And as you can see from the red dots here, which are volcanoes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 131438.0,
      "end_time": 134256.0,
      "text": "we don&#39;t have volcanoes in the Amazon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 134280.0,
      "end_time": 136980.0,
      "text": "nor in most of Peru."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 136122.0,
      "end_time": 140390.0,
      "text": "So it follows: We should not expect to see a boiling river."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 141660.0,
      "end_time": 145748.0,
      "text": "Telling this same story at a family dinner,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 145772.0,
      "end_time": 148242.0,
      "text": "my aunt tells me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 148266.0,
      "end_time": 152248.0,
      "text": "\"But no, Andrés, I&#39;ve been there. I&#39;ve swum in that river.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 152898.0,
      "end_time": 156535.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 156559.0,
      "end_time": 158306.0,
      "text": "Then my uncle jumps in."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 158330.0,
      "end_time": 161600.0,
      "text": "\"No, Andrés, she&#39;s not kidding."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 161840.0,
      "end_time": 165670.0,
      "text": "You see, you can only swim in it after a very heavy rain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 165910.0,
      "end_time": 168337.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s protected by a powerful shaman."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 168361.0,
      "end_time": 170678.0,
      "text": "Your aunt, she&#39;s friends with his wife.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 171257.0,
      "end_time": 173620.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 173860.0,
      "end_time": 174237.0,
      "text": "\"¿Cómo?\" [\"Huh?\"]"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 174261.0,
      "end_time": 176475.0,
      "text": "You know, despite all my scientific skepticism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 176499.0,
      "end_time": 180930.0,
      "text": "I found myself hiking into the jungle, guided by my aunt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 180955.0,
      "end_time": 184852.0,
      "text": "over 700 kilometers away from the nearest volcanic center,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 184876.0,
      "end_time": 188494.0,
      "text": "and well, honestly, mentally preparing myself"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 188518.0,
      "end_time": 192894.0,
      "text": "to behold the legendary \"warm stream of the Amazon.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 194671.0,
      "end_time": 196292.0,
      "text": "But then ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 196316.0,
      "end_time": 197638.0,
      "text": "I heard something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 199255.0,
      "end_time": 200704.0,
      "text": "a low surge"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 202347.0,
      "end_time": 205420.0,
      "text": "that got louder and louder"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 205792.0,
      "end_time": 207260.0,
      "text": "as we came closer."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 208300.0,
      "end_time": 212228.0,
      "text": "It sounded like ocean waves constantly crashing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 212252.0,
      "end_time": 216937.0,
      "text": "and as we got closer, I saw smoke, vapor, coming up through the trees."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 216961.0,
      "end_time": 220260.0,
      "text": "And then, I saw this."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 221791.0,
      "end_time": 224260.0,
      "text": "I immediately grabbed for my thermometer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 224284.0,
      "end_time": 227560.0,
      "text": "and the average temperatures in the river"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 227585.0,
      "end_time": 229572.0,
      "text": "were 86 degrees C."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 231540.0,
      "end_time": 234807.0,
      "text": "This is not quite the 100-degree C boiling"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 234831.0,
      "end_time": 237708.0,
      "text": "but definitely close enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 238296.0,
      "end_time": 241388.0,
      "text": "The river flowed hot and fast."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 242181.0,
      "end_time": 245829.0,
      "text": "I followed it upriver and was led by, actually, the shaman&#39;s apprentice"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 245853.0,
      "end_time": 247637.0,
      "text": "to the most sacred site on the river."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 247661.0,
      "end_time": 249670.0,
      "text": "And this is what&#39;s bizarre --"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 249910.0,
      "end_time": 251730.0,
      "text": "It starts off as a cold stream."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 251502.0,
      "end_time": 253739.0,
      "text": "And here, at this site,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 253763.0,
      "end_time": 255930.0,
      "text": "is the home of the Yacumama,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 255954.0,
      "end_time": 259297.0,
      "text": "mother of the waters, a giant serpent spirit"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 259321.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261394.00000000003,
      "text": "who births hot and cold water."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 262150.0,
      "end_time": 266426.0,
      "text": "And here we find a hot spring,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 266451.0,
      "end_time": 271809.0,
      "text": "mixing with cold stream water underneath her protective motherly jaws"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 271833.0,
      "end_time": 275780.0,
      "text": "and thus bringing their legends to life."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 276283.0,
      "end_time": 278261.0,
      "text": "The next morning, I woke up and --"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 278285.0,
      "end_time": 280504.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 280528.0,
      "end_time": 282559.0,
      "text": "I asked for tea."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 282583.0,
      "end_time": 284823.0,
      "text": "I was handed a mug, a tea bag"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 284847.0,
      "end_time": 287174.0,
      "text": "and, well, pointed towards the river."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 288750.0,
      "end_time": 292584.0,
      "text": "To my surprise, the water was clean and had a pleasant taste,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 292608.0,
      "end_time": 295602.0,
      "text": "which is a little weird for geothermal systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 296441.0,
      "end_time": 297989.0,
      "text": "What was amazing"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 298130.0,
      "end_time": 300996.0,
      "text": "is that the locals had always known about this place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 301210.0,
      "end_time": 304725.0,
      "text": "and that I was by no means the first outsider to see it."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 305701.0,
      "end_time": 308638.0,
      "text": "It was just part of their everyday life."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 309115.0,
      "end_time": 311809.0,
      "text": "They drink its water."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 311833.0,
      "end_time": 314388.0,
      "text": "They take in its vapor."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 314412.0,
      "end_time": 316102.0,
      "text": "They cook with it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 316127.0,
      "end_time": 317637.0,
      "text": "clean with it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 317661.0,
      "end_time": 319459.0,
      "text": "even make their medicines with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 321940.0,
      "end_time": 322840.0,
      "text": "I met the shaman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 322864.0,
      "end_time": 327530.0,
      "text": "and he seemed like an extension of the river and his jungle."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 327848.0,
      "end_time": 329672.0,
      "text": "He asked for my intentions"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 330609.0,
      "end_time": 332188.0,
      "text": "and listened carefully."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 333262.0,
      "end_time": 336373.0,
      "text": "Then, to my tremendous relief --"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 336397.0,
      "end_time": 339944.0,
      "text": "I was freaking out, to be honest with you --"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 339968.0,
      "end_time": 344247.0,
      "text": "a smile began to snake across his face, and he just laughed."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 344271.0,
      "end_time": 346568.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 347796.0,
      "end_time": 352391.0,
      "text": "I had received the shaman&#39;s blessing to study the river,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 352415.0,
      "end_time": 355819.0,
      "text": "on the condition that after I take the water samples"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 355843.0,
      "end_time": 357359.0,
      "text": "and analyze them in my lab,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 357383.0,
      "end_time": 359193.0,
      "text": "wherever I was in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 360265.0,
      "end_time": 364310.0,
      "text": "that I pour the waters back into the ground"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 364550.0,
      "end_time": 366102.0,
      "text": "so that, as the shaman said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 366126.0,
      "end_time": 368871.0,
      "text": "the waters could find their way back home."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 371272.0,
      "end_time": 374859.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve been back every year since that first visit in 2011,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 374883.0,
      "end_time": 378308.0,
      "text": "and the fieldwork has been exhilarating,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 378332.0,
      "end_time": 382129.0,
      "text": "demanding and at times dangerous."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 382913.0,
      "end_time": 386128.0,
      "text": "One story was even featured in National Geographic Magazine."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 386152.0,
      "end_time": 390239.0,
      "text": "I was trapped on a small rock about the size of a sheet of paper"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 390263.0,
      "end_time": 392303.0,
      "text": "in sandals and board shorts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 392327.0,
      "end_time": 394733.0,
      "text": "in between an 80 degree C river"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 394757.0,
      "end_time": 398486.0,
      "text": "and a hot spring that, well, looked like this, close to boiling."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 399700.0,
      "end_time": 402608.0,
      "text": "And on top of that, it was Amazon rain forest."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 403206.0,
      "end_time": 405712.0,
      "text": "Pshh, pouring rain, couldn&#39;t see a thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 405736.0,
      "end_time": 409298.0,
      "text": "The temperature differential made it all white. It was a whiteout."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 410956.0,
      "end_time": 412361.0,
      "text": "Intense."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 414158.0,
      "end_time": 416596.0,
      "text": "Now, after years of work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 416620.0,
      "end_time": 422262.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll soon be submitting my geophysical and geochemical studies for publication."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 423470.0,
      "end_time": 427220.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;d like to share, today, with all of you here, on the TED stage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 427460.0,
      "end_time": 430236.0,
      "text": "for the first time, some of these discoveries."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 431340.0,
      "end_time": 433871.0,
      "text": "Well, first off, it&#39;s not a legend."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 434468.0,
      "end_time": 435642.0,
      "text": "Surprise!"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 435666.0,
      "end_time": 437991.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 438150.0,
      "end_time": 440529.0,
      "text": "When I first started the research,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 440553.0,
      "end_time": 443532.0,
      "text": "the satellite imagery was too low-resolution to be meaningful."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 443556.0,
      "end_time": 445183.0,
      "text": "There were just no good maps."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 445754.0,
      "end_time": 448145.0,
      "text": "Thanks to the support of the Google Earth team,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 448169.0,
      "end_time": 449514.0,
      "text": "I now have this."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 451251.0,
      "end_time": 456601.0,
      "text": "Not only that, the indigenous name of the river, Shanay-timpishka,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 457538.0,
      "end_time": 460268.0,
      "text": "\"boiled with the heat of the sun,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 461540.0,
      "end_time": 466919.0,
      "text": "indicating that I&#39;m not the first to wonder why the river boils,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 466943.0,
      "end_time": 470169.0,
      "text": "and showing that humanity has always sought to explain"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 470194.0,
      "end_time": 471733.0,
      "text": "the world around us."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 473526.0,
      "end_time": 475924.0,
      "text": "So why does the river boil?"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 475948.0,
      "end_time": 480361.0,
      "text": "(Bubbling sounds)"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 480385.0,
      "end_time": 482880.0,
      "text": "It actually took me three years to get that footage."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 484879.0,
      "end_time": 486484.0,
      "text": "Fault-fed hot springs."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 487625.0,
      "end_time": 491258.0,
      "text": "As we have hot blood running through our veins and arteries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 491282.0,
      "end_time": 496330.0,
      "text": "so, too, the earth has hot water running through its cracks and faults."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 497162.0,
      "end_time": 500757.0,
      "text": "Where these arteries come to the surface, these earth arteries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 500781.0,
      "end_time": 503155.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ll get geothermal manifestations:"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 503179.0,
      "end_time": 507198.0,
      "text": "fumaroles, hot springs and in our case, the boiling river."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 508459.0,
      "end_time": 512558.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s truly incredible, though, is the scale of this place."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 513221.0,
      "end_time": 515567.0,
      "text": "Next time you cross the road, think about this."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 516527.00000000006,
      "end_time": 519199.00000000006,
      "text": "The river flows wider than a two-lane road"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 519222.0,
      "end_time": 521870.0,
      "text": "along most of its path."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 521674.0,
      "end_time": 527160.0,
      "text": "It flows hot for 6.24 kilometers."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 528223.0,
      "end_time": 529732.0,
      "text": "Truly impressive."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 531770.0,
      "end_time": 534770.0,
      "text": "There are thermal pools larger than this TED stage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 534101.0,
      "end_time": 536577.0,
      "text": "and that waterfall that you see there"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 536601.0,
      "end_time": 538639.0,
      "text": "is six meters tall --"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 539384.0,
      "end_time": 542676.0,
      "text": "and all with near-boiling water."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 544243.0,
      "end_time": 546299.0,
      "text": "We mapped the temperatures along the river,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 546323.0,
      "end_time": 549441.0,
      "text": "and this was by far the most demanding part of the fieldwork."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 549866.0,
      "end_time": 553553.0,
      "text": "And the results were just awesome."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 553577.0,
      "end_time": 556730.0,
      "text": "Sorry -- the geoscientist in me coming out."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 556754.0,
      "end_time": 559180.0,
      "text": "And it showed this amazing trend."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 559204.0,
      "end_time": 561420.0,
      "text": "You see, the river starts off cold."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 561444.0,
      "end_time": 564439.0,
      "text": "It then heats up, cools back down, heats up, cools back down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 564463.0,
      "end_time": 567810.0,
      "text": "heats up again, and then has this beautiful decay curve"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 567105.0,
      "end_time": 569477.0,
      "text": "until it smashes into this cold river."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 570539.0,
      "end_time": 573333.0,
      "text": "Now, I understand not all of you are geothermal scientists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 573357.0,
      "end_time": 575582.0,
      "text": "so to put it in more everyday terms:"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 576225.0,
      "end_time": 578358.0,
      "text": "Everyone loves coffee."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 578382.0,
      "end_time": 579651.0,
      "text": "Yes? Good."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 580517.0,
      "end_time": 584200.0,
      "text": "Your regular cup of coffee, 54 degrees C,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 584224.0,
      "end_time": 586334.0,
      "text": "an extra-hot one, well, 60."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 586896.0,
      "end_time": 589670.0,
      "text": "So, put in coffee shop terms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 589910.0,
      "end_time": 591654.0,
      "text": "the boiling river plots like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 592401.0,
      "end_time": 593900.0,
      "text": "There you have your hot coffee."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 594906.0,
      "end_time": 596630.0,
      "text": "Here you have your extra-hot coffee,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 596654.0,
      "end_time": 598828.0,
      "text": "and you can see that there&#39;s a bit point there"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 598852.0,
      "end_time": 601840.0,
      "text": "where the river is still hotter than even the extra-hot coffee."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 601864.0,
      "end_time": 603856.0,
      "text": "And these are average water temperatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 603880.0,
      "end_time": 608790.0,
      "text": "We took these in the dry season to ensure the purest geothermal temperatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 608603.0,
      "end_time": 611223.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s a magic number here that&#39;s not being shown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 611247.0,
      "end_time": 613776.0,
      "text": "and that number is 47 degrees C,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 614856.0,
      "end_time": 617378.0,
      "text": "because that&#39;s where things start to hurt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 617402.0,
      "end_time": 621575.0,
      "text": "and I know this from very personal experience."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 622186.0,
      "end_time": 625120.0,
      "text": "Above that temperature, you don&#39;t want to get in that water."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 625360.0,
      "end_time": 626698.0,
      "text": "You need to be careful."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 626722.0,
      "end_time": 628370.0,
      "text": "It can be deadly."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 628704.0,
      "end_time": 630995.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve seen all sorts of animals fall in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 631190.0,
      "end_time": 635198.0,
      "text": "and what&#39;s shocking to me, is the process is pretty much the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 635898.0,
      "end_time": 638579.0,
      "text": "So they fall in and the first thing to go are the eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 638603.0,
      "end_time": 641969.0,
      "text": "Eyes, apparently, cook very quickly. They turn this milky-white color."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 641994.0,
      "end_time": 643344.0,
      "text": "The stream is carrying them."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 643368.0,
      "end_time": 646431.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re trying to swim out, but their meat is cooking on the bone"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 646455.0,
      "end_time": 647621.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s so hot."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 647645.0,
      "end_time": 649490.0,
      "text": "So they&#39;re losing power, losing power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 649514.0,
      "end_time": 652904.0,
      "text": "until finally they get to a point where hot water goes into their mouths"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 652928.0,
      "end_time": 655149.0,
      "text": "and they cook from the inside out."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 655440.0,
      "end_time": 660672.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 660696.0,
      "end_time": 662815.0,
      "text": "A bit sadistic, aren&#39;t we?"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 662839.0,
      "end_time": 664179.0,
      "text": "Jeez."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 665362.0,
      "end_time": 667980.0,
      "text": "Leave them marinating for a little longer."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 669468.0,
      "end_time": 672195.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s, again, amazing are these temperatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 672220.0,
      "end_time": 675698.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re similar to things that I&#39;ve seen on volcanoes all over the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 675722.0,
      "end_time": 678259.0,
      "text": "and even super-volcanoes like Yellowstone."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 678896.0,
      "end_time": 680204.0,
      "text": "But here&#39;s the thing:"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 682173.0,
      "end_time": 687172.0,
      "text": "the data is showing that the boiling river exists"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 687196.0,
      "end_time": 689486.0,
      "text": "independent of volcanism."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 690491.0,
      "end_time": 693911.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s neither magmatic or volcanic in origin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 695722.0,
      "end_time": 701925.0,
      "text": "and again, over 700 kilometers away from the nearest volcanic center."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 702543.0,
      "end_time": 706909.0,
      "text": "How can a boiling river exist like this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 707790.0,
      "end_time": 710945.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve asked geothermal experts and volcanologists for years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 710970.0,
      "end_time": 715787.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m still unable to find another non-volcanic geothermal system"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 715811.0,
      "end_time": 717378.0,
      "text": "of this magnitude."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 719121.0,
      "end_time": 720645.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s unique."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 721489.0,
      "end_time": 724931.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s special on a global scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 726708.0,
      "end_time": 729175.0,
      "text": "So, still -- how does it work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 730460.0,
      "end_time": 732596.0,
      "text": "Where do we get this heat?"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 733186.0,
      "end_time": 735279.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s still more research to be done"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 735303.0,
      "end_time": 738492.0,
      "text": "to better constrain the problem and better understand the system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 738516.0,
      "end_time": 740842.0,
      "text": "but from what the data is telling us now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 740866.0,
      "end_time": 744230.0,
      "text": "it looks to be the result of a large hydrothermal system."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 745151.0,
      "end_time": 746611.0,
      "text": "Basically, it works like this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 746635.0,
      "end_time": 749943.0,
      "text": "So, the deeper you go into the earth, the hotter it gets."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 749967.0,
      "end_time": 752595.0,
      "text": "We refer to this as the geothermal gradient."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 753460.0,
      "end_time": 758388.0,
      "text": "The waters could be coming from as far away as glaciers in the Andes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 758412.0,
      "end_time": 760411.0,
      "text": "then seeping down deep into the earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 760435.0,
      "end_time": 763202.0,
      "text": "and coming out to form the boiling river"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 763226.0,
      "end_time": 766233.0,
      "text": "after getting heated up from the geothermal gradient,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 767311.0,
      "end_time": 769550.0,
      "text": "all due to this unique geologic setting."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 770587.0,
      "end_time": 773434.0,
      "text": "Now, we found that in and around the river --"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 773458.0,
      "end_time": 774951.0,
      "text": "this is working with colleagues"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 774975.0,
      "end_time": 777620.0,
      "text": "from National Geographic, Dr. Spencer Wells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 777860.0,
      "end_time": 779796.0,
      "text": "and Dr. Jon Eisen from UC Davis --"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 779820.0,
      "end_time": 783820.0,
      "text": "we genetically sequenced the extremophile lifeforms"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 783106.0,
      "end_time": 787710.0,
      "text": "living in and around the river, and have found new lifeforms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 787734.0,
      "end_time": 791149.0,
      "text": "unique species living in the boiling river."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 792264.0,
      "end_time": 797507.0,
      "text": "But again, despite all of these studies, all of these discoveries and the legends,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 798499.0,
      "end_time": 799499.0,
      "text": "a question remains:"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 801704.0,
      "end_time": 804623.0,
      "text": "What is the significance of the boiling river?"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 806601.0,
      "end_time": 811247.0,
      "text": "What is the significance of this stationary cloud"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 811271.0,
      "end_time": 814146.0,
      "text": "that always hovers over this patch of jungle?"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 815333.0,
      "end_time": 817983.0,
      "text": "And what is the significance"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 818700.0,
      "end_time": 820989.0,
      "text": "of a detail in a childhood legend?"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 823547.0,
      "end_time": 826655.0,
      "text": "To the shaman and his community, it&#39;s a sacred site."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 827414.0,
      "end_time": 829759.0,
      "text": "To me, as a geoscientist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 829783.0,
      "end_time": 832626.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s a unique geothermal phenomenon."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 834740.0,
      "end_time": 837771.0,
      "text": "But to the illegal loggers and cattle farmers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 837796.0,
      "end_time": 841439.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s just another resource to exploit."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 842820.0,
      "end_time": 846607.0,
      "text": "And to the Peruvian government, it&#39;s just another stretch"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 846631.0,
      "end_time": 852574.0,
      "text": "of unprotected land ready for development."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 854186.0,
      "end_time": 857782.0,
      "text": "My goal is to ensure that whoever controls this land"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 857806.0,
      "end_time": 861924.0,
      "text": "understands the boiling river&#39;s uniqueness and significance."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 862892.0,
      "end_time": 864630.0,
      "text": "Because that&#39;s the question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 865853.0,
      "end_time": 867487.0,
      "text": "one of significance."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 868568.0,
      "end_time": 870896.0,
      "text": "And the thing there is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 872110.0,
      "end_time": 874191.0,
      "text": "we define significance."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 874998.0,
      "end_time": 877658.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s us. We have that power."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 877682.0,
      "end_time": 880410.0,
      "text": "We are the ones who draw that line"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 880434.0,
      "end_time": 882781.0,
      "text": "between the sacred and the trivial."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 883736.0,
      "end_time": 886120.0,
      "text": "And in this age,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 886360.0,
      "end_time": 889534.0,
      "text": "where everything seems mapped, measured and studied,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 891290.0,
      "end_time": 893756.0,
      "text": "in this age of information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 894899.0,
      "end_time": 898471.0,
      "text": "I remind you all that discoveries are not just made"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 898495.0,
      "end_time": 903580.0,
      "text": "in the black void of the unknown"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 904153.0,
      "end_time": 907562.0,
      "text": "but in the white noise of overwhelming data."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 909862.0,
      "end_time": 912847.0,
      "text": "There remains so much to explore."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 913958.0,
      "end_time": 917453.0,
